WEBVTT

00:10.479 --> 00:13.281
[ Droid Language ]

00:13.283 --> 00:17.785
Right. Like I'd
let a droid tell me
how to play sabacc.

00:17.787 --> 00:19.354
I'm in.

00:19.356 --> 00:22.156
[ Angry Chattering ]

00:22.158 --> 00:24.559
Hey, it doesn't have to
be a big job, Jho.

00:24.561 --> 00:27.362
Just something
to put fuel in the <i> Ghost</i>
and food in our bellies.

00:27.364 --> 00:30.131
Sorry, Kanan.
Got nothing.

00:30.133 --> 00:32.800
But the stranger playing
with Zeb over there...

00:32.802 --> 00:35.770
said he was looking
to hire a ship and crew.

00:35.772 --> 00:37.539
Go talk to him.

00:41.644 --> 00:44.045
[ Angry Grunt ]

00:44.047 --> 00:45.713
Guess it's down
to you and me.

00:45.715 --> 00:50.785
Except-- [ Nervous Chuckle ]
it seems I'm all outta creds.

00:50.787 --> 00:53.187
[ Mocking Sound ]

00:53.189 --> 00:55.790
So, I'll bet my droid.

00:55.792 --> 00:59.260
- [ Chatters ]
- Whoa. You can't bet Chopper.
He's--

00:59.262 --> 01:01.362
[ Whistles ]
See?

01:01.364 --> 01:04.065
I can't lose. And you know
we need the credits.

01:04.066 --> 01:05.800
- Right.
- [ Angry Grunt ]

01:07.269 --> 01:10.271
- Do it.
- [ Angry Chattering ]

01:10.273 --> 01:12.440
So, do we have a bet?

01:12.442 --> 01:15.343
[ Laughing ]
We do.

01:15.345 --> 01:18.112
Sabacc!
[ Laughing ]

01:18.114 --> 01:19.781
I win.

01:19.783 --> 01:21.549
Not so fast.

01:21.551 --> 01:23.785
It appears
I have an Idiot's Array.

01:24.820 --> 01:27.088
Which makes you, well--

01:27.090 --> 01:30.224
[ Growls ]
And what does that make you?

01:30.226 --> 01:33.628
Name's Calrissian.
Lando Calrissian.

01:33.630 --> 01:37.532
Now please, introduce me
to my new droid.

01:45.875 --> 01:47.108
[ Droid Language ]

01:48.344 --> 01:52.013
- Hi. I can explain.
- Explain what?

01:52.015 --> 01:53.982
Hera, Sabine, Ezra.

01:53.984 --> 01:56.051
This is Lando Calrissian.

01:56.053 --> 01:59.187
He needs a fast ship to move
some cargo past the Imperial
blockade of Lothal.

01:59.189 --> 02:04.292
Yes. For some reason,
this planet has an unusually
large Imperial presence.

02:07.063 --> 02:10.131
But are you sure
you can get this vessel
past the blockade,

02:10.133 --> 02:12.234
Captain... Hera,
is it?

02:12.236 --> 02:16.271
It is. And the <i> Ghost </i> can mask
both its signal and signature.

02:16.273 --> 02:18.073
We'll get you past
the blockade.

02:18.075 --> 02:21.276
- What's the cargo?
- I was told
"No questions asked."

02:21.278 --> 02:23.445
That's fine.
It just costs more.

02:23.447 --> 02:25.981
Kanan and I already
settled on a price.

02:25.983 --> 02:28.783
But I assume
he requires your approval.

02:28.785 --> 02:31.319
- He doesn't.
- Excellent.

02:31.321 --> 02:33.922
When the job's done,
you'll be paid handsomely,

02:33.924 --> 02:36.958
and, as agreed,
I'll return your droid.

02:36.960 --> 02:38.893
Return our... droid?

02:38.895 --> 02:40.929
[ Angry Chattering ]

02:40.931 --> 02:43.231
Uh, yeah. Funny story.

02:43.233 --> 02:45.934
You see, Lando and I
were playing sabacc,

02:45.936 --> 02:49.771
and I kinda... bet Chopper.

02:49.773 --> 02:53.074
Garazeb Orrelios,
Chopper wasn't yours to bet!

02:53.076 --> 02:55.076
Kanan said it was okay.

02:55.078 --> 02:58.179
And you should know better!
Chopper is a member
of this crew!

02:58.181 --> 03:00.282
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
We should go.

03:00.284 --> 03:03.551
I need to pick up my cargo,
and I don't want to keep
my supplier waiting.

03:03.553 --> 03:05.387
Besides,
if all goes well,

03:05.389 --> 03:09.057
there won't be anything
for you good people
to argue about.

03:09.059 --> 03:10.025
[ Groans ]

03:25.141 --> 03:27.976
Oh, you're quite
the pilot.

03:27.978 --> 03:31.079
That's the smoothest takeoff
I've had in years.

03:31.081 --> 03:33.148
And you're quite
the smooth-talking
smuggler.

03:33.150 --> 03:35.517
"Smuggler"?
Such a small word.

03:35.519 --> 03:39.120
I'm more of
a... galactic entrepreneur.

03:41.123 --> 03:43.124
That means businessperson.

03:43.126 --> 03:45.327
I know what it means.

03:45.329 --> 03:48.997
Chopper, I need you to fix
the signature modulator so
we can get past the blockade.

03:48.999 --> 03:51.366
[ Droid Language ]

03:51.368 --> 03:54.369
Chopper's right.
He's no longer a part
of the crew.

03:54.371 --> 03:56.371
He doesn't have to do
what you tell him anymore.

03:56.373 --> 03:59.040
I can see you have
some things to work out.

03:59.042 --> 04:00.842
I wonder, my new friend,

04:00.844 --> 04:04.379
if you'd be kind enough
to give me a tour
of this fine ship.

04:04.381 --> 04:07.048
[ Droid Language ]

04:09.518 --> 04:11.152
[ Droid Language ]

04:16.926 --> 04:19.594
[ Droid Language Continues ]

04:19.596 --> 04:21.995
Why, thank you, Chopper.

04:21.998 --> 04:25.433
Can't believe the little
bolt bucket's actually
waiting on that guy.

04:25.435 --> 04:27.535
I can't believe
you lost Chopper.

04:27.537 --> 04:29.437
Good thing I wasn't there.
You'd have bet me.

04:29.439 --> 04:32.207
Mmm, nah. You wouldn't
have covered the pot.

04:32.209 --> 04:34.609
Besides, I think
Calrissian cheated.

04:34.611 --> 04:37.412
You're just a sore loser.
Lando seems nice enough.

04:37.414 --> 04:39.514
I'm telling you,
I don't like that guy.

04:40.616 --> 04:44.052
Sabine. I understand
this is your work.

04:44.054 --> 04:47.989
Reminds me of Janyor's
protest paintings on Bith.

04:47.991 --> 04:50.458
Janyor of Bith
is a major influence.

04:50.460 --> 04:55.029
Well, your work
is even more stunning
in its simplicity.

04:55.031 --> 04:57.465
Hey, I told you your stuff
was good months ago.

04:57.467 --> 05:00.068
Yeah, but you
didn't know why.
[ Clicks Tongue ]

05:00.070 --> 05:03.071
Oh, milady,
that's hardly fair.

05:03.073 --> 05:06.474
He's just a child
with no experience
of the galaxy.

05:06.476 --> 05:10.478
I, um-- I don't suppose
you'd like to see my more
impressionistic pieces?

05:10.480 --> 05:14.015
I happen to be
an impressionistic
connoisseur.

05:14.017 --> 05:16.418
That means--
I know what it means.

05:20.189 --> 05:22.957
Hey, what does that mean?
A lot less
than he thinks.

05:22.959 --> 05:24.025
I don't like that guy.

05:34.670 --> 05:36.671
<i>Merchant-One,</i>
this is Calrissian.

05:36.673 --> 05:38.940
Requesting permission
to dock.

05:38.942 --> 05:41.276
<i>[ Male Voice ]</i>
<i>You have the goods?</i>

05:41.278 --> 05:43.077
Always.

05:43.079 --> 05:46.948
<i>Ah, then permission granted.</i>

05:52.388 --> 05:56.024
Now, whatever I say,
just play along.

05:56.026 --> 05:57.292
Wait.
What does that mean?

05:59.762 --> 06:02.530
I hope you have
a backup plan in case
something goes wrong.

06:02.532 --> 06:07.735
No fear, Captain.
If a comet hits,
this ship has escape pods.

06:07.737 --> 06:10.371
That's not exactly
the kind of "wrong"
I had in mind.

06:14.076 --> 06:17.178
Good to see you again,
Azmorigan.

06:22.384 --> 06:24.352
I have what you ordered.

06:26.555 --> 06:28.089
Mmm, mmm.

06:28.091 --> 06:31.426
What do you have
to offer in return?

06:31.428 --> 06:34.762
Her name is Hera.
[ Gasps ]

06:34.764 --> 06:36.030
What?

06:41.203 --> 06:42.437
You can't do this!

06:42.439 --> 06:45.073
Trust me.
Hera!

06:45.075 --> 06:47.509
A deal's a deal, Kanan.

06:48.444 --> 06:50.345
[ Grumbling ]

06:50.347 --> 06:55.283
Well, her attire
is, uh, preposterous,

06:55.285 --> 06:59.854
but the trade is,
uh, mmm-- is acceptable.

07:05.060 --> 07:08.363
Thank you, Lord Calrissian,
for delivering me
to my new master.

07:08.365 --> 07:11.032
I must find a way
to repay you.

07:11.034 --> 07:13.134
Please don't let it
concern you.

07:13.136 --> 07:14.769
Enough prattle.

07:14.771 --> 07:17.372
Eh, you disturb my supper.

07:17.374 --> 07:19.474
[ Belches ]
Uh, take your cargo and go.

07:19.476 --> 07:24.045
As always, Azmorigan,
a pleasure doing business
with you.

07:35.257 --> 07:37.091
Where's Hera?

07:38.294 --> 07:40.361
Tell her about Hera,
Lando.

07:41.363 --> 07:43.631
Hera is following
the plan,

07:43.633 --> 07:47.468
which is what we should be doing
if we want to get her back.

07:47.470 --> 07:50.138
- Where's Hera?
- What plan is she following?

07:50.140 --> 07:52.840
- I told her
to take an escape pod.
- You never told her that.

07:52.842 --> 07:55.643
I did, actually.
Weren't you paying attention?

07:55.645 --> 07:58.246
Besides, Hera strikes me
as very capable.

07:58.248 --> 08:00.415
We are lucky to have
a captain like her.

08:00.417 --> 08:01.716
I know that.

08:01.718 --> 08:04.385
Wait.
What do you mean, "we"?

08:04.387 --> 08:08.590
Quite a day you're having.
First, you lose Chopper,
now Hera.

08:17.733 --> 08:19.167
What's in here?

08:19.169 --> 08:21.202
Sophisticated
mining equipment.

08:21.204 --> 08:22.837
[ Snorting ]

08:22.839 --> 08:26.240
Uh, sounds like
your sophisticated mining
equipment is snoring.

08:26.242 --> 08:28.109
Just don't open the box.

08:28.111 --> 08:30.411
And whatever you do,
keep it calm.

08:31.547 --> 08:33.780
[ Droid Language ]

08:40.389 --> 08:42.523
Ah.
[ Smacking ]

08:42.525 --> 08:45.193
[ Slurping ]

08:45.195 --> 08:46.427
[ Hawks, Spits ]

08:48.263 --> 08:49.397
You need food?

08:49.399 --> 08:51.799
I seem to have lost
my appetite.

08:51.801 --> 08:54.168
But perhaps you'd like me
to serve <i> you.</i>

08:55.204 --> 08:57.205
Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes.

08:57.207 --> 09:00.808
Good practice for you.
Uh, serve me, serve me.

09:00.810 --> 09:03.678
[ Stammering ]
Be quick about it.

09:05.881 --> 09:08.683
And perhaps you'd prefer
to dine alone?

09:09.785 --> 09:12.186
Mmm. Oh, yes.

09:12.188 --> 09:15.490
Go, go. Leave us.

09:15.492 --> 09:17.558
Beat it!
[ Doors Close ]

09:18.927 --> 09:22.497
- Take the whole tray.
- What are you talking about?

09:22.499 --> 09:23.898
[ Gasps ]

09:27.436 --> 09:27.802
[ Groans ]

09:31.674 --> 09:33.775
The master desires
a little more alone time...

09:33.777 --> 09:36.711
while I change clothes
in my quarters.

09:42.451 --> 09:44.419
[ Thump ]

09:45.654 --> 09:47.355
That was
a really useful tray.

09:49.792 --> 09:52.627
That Twi'lek's my property,

09:52.629 --> 09:56.431
and I want my property
back here <i> now!</i>

10:02.938 --> 10:04.372
[ Powering Up ]

10:11.580 --> 10:13.748
In a pod, as discussed.

10:13.750 --> 10:16.417
You really should have
more faith in our captain.

10:16.419 --> 10:17.919
<i>Our </i> captain?

10:17.921 --> 10:20.488
Um, we'll go prep
the airlock.

10:39.808 --> 10:41.976
<i>[ Sabine On Comm ]</i>
<i>Kanan, Hera's aboard.</i>

10:41.978 --> 10:44.645
<i>[ Lando On Comm ]</i>
<i>We should probably</i>
<i>make ourselves scarce.</i>

10:44.647 --> 10:45.747
Somebody should.

10:56.792 --> 11:00.561
You played that perfectly.
Thank you.

11:00.563 --> 11:01.896
Oh, you're welcome.

11:02.965 --> 11:05.867
[ Coughing ]
I deserved that.

11:05.869 --> 11:08.803
But can we get back
to the job at hand--

11:08.805 --> 11:11.372
flying us past
the Imperial blockade?

11:11.374 --> 11:14.609
Otherwise,
I don't have to pay you
or give your droid back.

11:16.879 --> 11:18.713
What was in that crate?

11:18.715 --> 11:20.882
Come on. I'll show you.

11:20.884 --> 11:23.751
Calrissian said
not to open it.

11:23.753 --> 11:26.521
Yes. [ Chuckles ]
He did.

11:27.689 --> 11:28.923
[ Grunts ]

11:30.392 --> 11:31.859
[ Snorting ]

11:33.595 --> 11:38.733
Uh, kinda cute,
whatever it is.

11:38.735 --> 11:40.334
- [ Sniffing ]
- [ Squealing ]

11:42.871 --> 11:44.438
Catch it!

11:47.976 --> 11:49.744
[ Squealing ]

11:51.413 --> 11:53.815
[ Snorts ]
That's what was
in the crate.

11:55.751 --> 11:57.985
Grab that puffer-pig,
but don't scare her.

11:59.788 --> 12:02.824
- Got her!
- You're scaring her!
I told you not to scare her.

12:02.826 --> 12:04.992
I'm not scaring her!

12:07.462 --> 12:08.563
Karabast!

12:09.898 --> 12:11.599
Whoa.
Whoa!

12:11.601 --> 12:14.769
- You see? You scared her.
- What is going on out here?

12:14.771 --> 12:17.405
It's a, um, puffer--

12:17.407 --> 12:18.873
I don't want to know.

12:24.613 --> 12:26.447
We've reached the blockade.

12:26.449 --> 12:28.649
I could really use Hera
on this side of the pig
right about now.

12:28.651 --> 12:31.485
Yeah, I don't see
that happening.

12:31.487 --> 12:34.789
Any idea what the Imperials
are hoping to find
with this blockade?

12:34.791 --> 12:37.058
Rebels?
Besides that.

12:37.060 --> 12:39.927
Unauthorized mining
equipment, perhaps.

12:39.929 --> 12:42.897
And why would they
be looking for that?

12:42.899 --> 12:46.767
Maybe because
I tried smuggling some
here a week ago.

12:47.970 --> 12:49.670
Don't worry.

12:49.672 --> 12:51.906
The Imperials are scanning
for equipment, machinery.

12:51.908 --> 12:55.443
But our girl here
is 100% organic.
[ Squeals ]

12:55.445 --> 12:57.578
Their scanners
won't detect her,

12:57.580 --> 13:00.882
so long as your ship
can mask its signature.

13:00.884 --> 13:03.651
You know it can't
until you ask Chopper
to fix it.

13:03.653 --> 13:05.820
[ Laughing ]
You're catching on.

13:05.822 --> 13:10.491
All right, my little friend.
Would you like to be a hero
and fix it for me?

13:10.493 --> 13:12.093
[ Droid Language ]

13:16.765 --> 13:17.732
Admiral.

13:21.169 --> 13:23.170
This Corellian ship
matches the description...

13:23.172 --> 13:25.106
of the rebel craft
we've been looking for.

13:28.944 --> 13:30.177
[ Beeps ]

13:30.179 --> 13:32.947
Okay, signature modulator's
back online.

13:32.949 --> 13:34.682
And just in time.

13:34.684 --> 13:37.818
No. Its signature reads
the freighter <i> Tontine,</i>

13:37.820 --> 13:40.821
authorized for travel
between Boz Pity and Lothal.

13:40.823 --> 13:43.090
<i>Tontine,</i>
prepare for scanning.

13:46.695 --> 13:49.497
[ Lando ]
Sabine, once we
get back to Lothal,

13:49.499 --> 13:51.999
I'd love to purchase
some of your art.

13:52.001 --> 13:55.736
[ Sabine ]
Really?
My work. You'd pay?

13:55.738 --> 13:57.505
Oh, he'll pay.

13:57.507 --> 14:00.508
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Scans clear, </i> Tontine.
<i>You may proceed.</i>

14:00.510 --> 14:02.677
We're gonna make it!

14:02.679 --> 14:04.211
[ Grunting ]

14:07.916 --> 14:08.916
[ Squealing ]

14:08.918 --> 14:11.686
Kid, not a good...

14:11.688 --> 14:13.020
idea.

14:13.022 --> 14:16.123
[ Button Clicks ]
[ Alarm Blaring ]

14:19.561 --> 14:22.930
The signature was masked.
That's the rebel ship!

14:22.932 --> 14:24.498
All ships open fire!

14:35.944 --> 14:40.081
Uh, Kanan,
when they shoot at us,
Hera usually shoots back.

14:40.083 --> 14:42.216
Yeah, well,
I'm not Hera,

14:42.218 --> 14:44.819
and I'm having enough trouble
just keeping ahead
of these guys.

14:44.821 --> 14:46.487
[ Laser Cannon Firing ]

14:51.660 --> 14:52.860
<i>[ Hera On Comm ]</i>
<i>Cloud cover!</i>
What?

14:52.862 --> 14:54.862
<i>Find some.</i>
Oh. Right.

15:19.921 --> 15:22.990
Good call, Hera.
I think we're in the clear.

15:22.992 --> 15:25.126
You know, your job's
a lot harder than it looks.

15:25.128 --> 15:28.162
Nice. He finally
appreciates you.

15:28.164 --> 15:30.998
All right. Enough with
the divide and conquer.

15:31.000 --> 15:33.034
You think by setting us
against each other,

15:33.036 --> 15:35.703
you'll keep us
off-balance enough
to get what you want.

15:35.705 --> 15:40.841
But what you want
depends on my crew
working together in sync.

15:40.843 --> 15:43.210
Is that clear?
As crystal, Captain.

15:43.212 --> 15:45.913
[ Grunts ]
A little help?

15:56.992 --> 15:58.893
This time,
try to keep it calm.

15:58.895 --> 16:00.661
We don't want you
inflating it again.

16:00.663 --> 16:03.097
Hey, it wasn't my fault.
It's your face's fault.

16:03.099 --> 16:04.799
This is your land?

16:04.801 --> 16:07.668
Bought if off
a charming fellow
named Vizago.

16:07.670 --> 16:11.272
Perfect. But why
was it so important
to get this pig here?

16:11.274 --> 16:14.809
Because a puffer-pig has a nose
for precious minerals.

16:14.811 --> 16:18.245
It can do the job
of a dozen mining scanners.

16:18.247 --> 16:21.916
And the Empire doesn't
want private landholders
mining Lothal.

16:21.918 --> 16:23.918
We're done here.
Pay us, and we'll
be on our way.

16:23.920 --> 16:26.120
[ Azmorigan ]
He has other debts to pay.

16:30.258 --> 16:31.892
Azmorigan?

16:31.894 --> 16:36.897
You forget
I introduced you
to Vizago, huh?

16:36.899 --> 16:39.133
I knew where
you were headed.

16:39.135 --> 16:41.902
But your ship--
You couldn't have hidden it
anywhere close.

16:41.904 --> 16:45.639
Did you... walk here?
You don't walk anywhere.

16:45.641 --> 16:47.908
Well, I do
what's necessary...

16:47.910 --> 16:51.946
to claim my property,
Calrissian.

16:51.948 --> 16:53.280
What do you want?

16:53.282 --> 16:55.950
My demands are simple.

16:55.952 --> 16:59.086
I want my pig back...
and you.

16:59.088 --> 17:03.124
Plus this ship and
this crew as compensation
for my sore feet.

17:03.126 --> 17:08.162
But first-- first,
I want to bury Calrissian.

17:08.164 --> 17:10.364
Yeah, yeah,
I understand
the feeling.

17:10.366 --> 17:12.633
But no.
Now, wait.

17:12.635 --> 17:14.734
Let's consider that
last demand for a sec.

17:14.737 --> 17:17.972
[ Grumbling ]

17:17.973 --> 17:20.875
I've run out of patience!
Get them!

17:20.877 --> 17:22.009
[ Blaster Fire ]

17:22.944 --> 17:24.044
Get back!

17:29.651 --> 17:31.952
Chopper, don't hide there!
It's a fuel canister!

17:39.327 --> 17:40.961
No lightsabers,
not unless we're--

17:40.963 --> 17:42.730
You worry too much.

17:46.801 --> 17:48.969
Hey, mine doesn't do that.

17:48.971 --> 17:52.740
Nope. I might not be able
to sword fight yet,
but I can shoot.

17:52.742 --> 17:54.742
Kid, you continue
to impress.

17:57.179 --> 17:58.412
Nice shot, Lando!

17:58.414 --> 18:00.481
Yeah, just not as much
as Lando.

18:03.985 --> 18:05.986
[ Grumbling ]

18:06.988 --> 18:10.057
[ Grunting,
Chittering ]

18:12.928 --> 18:14.261
[ Squeals ]

18:15.830 --> 18:18.399
- [ Squealing ]
- Zeb. The pig! Scare it!

18:18.401 --> 18:20.100
What? How?

18:20.102 --> 18:21.402
Just be <i> you.</i>

18:21.404 --> 18:24.171
- [ Squealing ]
- Hey, pig!

18:24.173 --> 18:25.339
[ Screeches ]

18:36.017 --> 18:37.184
[ Shouts ]

18:46.895 --> 18:49.930
[ Droid Language ]

18:49.932 --> 18:51.365
You're welcome!

18:59.874 --> 19:01.242
[ Groans ]

19:01.244 --> 19:06.080
New terms:
I get Calrissian,
and this one lives.

19:09.417 --> 19:13.988
I get Calrissian,
and you all can go free.

19:13.990 --> 19:15.522
You got it.
Deal.

19:15.524 --> 19:18.259
It's tempting,
but the answer's still no.

19:21.129 --> 19:23.063
[ Droid Language ]

19:24.299 --> 19:25.766
[ Yelps ]
Whoa!

19:30.338 --> 19:31.872
[ Chatters ]

19:33.108 --> 19:37.945
My terms:
You and your men leave now,
and we let you live.

19:37.947 --> 19:39.046
Start walking.

19:40.949 --> 19:42.049
[ Whimpering ]

19:51.426 --> 19:55.195
I like everything
that just happened except
that you let Azmorigan live.

19:55.197 --> 19:57.031
That'll be a problem
for me later.

19:57.033 --> 19:59.133
I think you have
a problem now.

19:59.135 --> 20:02.936
You don't have the credits
you owe us, do you?
In fact, you never did.

20:02.938 --> 20:05.973
But I will once my baby's
worked her magic.

20:05.975 --> 20:07.975
You mean, if she finds
what you're looking for...

20:07.977 --> 20:10.010
<i>and </i> you've mined
<i>and </i> smuggled it off-world?

20:10.012 --> 20:11.912
I can give you back
your droid.

20:11.914 --> 20:14.181
[ Chattering ]

20:14.183 --> 20:16.183
That won't satisfy
your debt to me.

20:16.185 --> 20:17.985
Not after
what you pulled.

20:17.987 --> 20:20.988
Then how about
we settle that debt with
a little game of sabacc?

20:20.990 --> 20:23.057
Then you'll just
have to owe me one.

20:28.897 --> 20:34.268
Don't worry,
my small metal friend.
We shall meet again.

20:34.270 --> 20:36.136
[ Angry Grunt ]

20:38.039 --> 20:40.507
Oh, come on.
I saved your circuits.

20:40.509 --> 20:41.975
Isn't that
apology enough?

20:41.977 --> 20:43.077
[ Blows Raspberry ]

20:45.213 --> 20:48.048
So that's it?
We just walk away
without the creds?

20:48.050 --> 20:49.450
Well, we got Chopper back.

20:49.452 --> 20:51.285
I'm looking
for a positive here.

20:51.287 --> 20:53.987
There are a lot of things
we couldn't accomplish
without him.

20:53.989 --> 20:55.155
You should appreciate
that more.

20:55.157 --> 20:57.224
I always appreciated you,
Sabine.

20:57.226 --> 20:59.693
Yes, Ezra, I know.

20:59.695 --> 21:01.662
Course, we still need
food and fuel.

21:01.664 --> 21:03.897
[ Chopper Hoots ]

21:05.100 --> 21:08.068
Oh, hey, Chopper
stole Lando's fuel!

21:08.070 --> 21:10.637
You mean
he was playing Lando
the whole time?

21:12.173 --> 21:13.907
Good job, Chopper.
[ Whooping ]

21:13.909 --> 21:15.976
[ Kanan ]
Anyone that fools Lando
is okay with me.

21:17.078 --> 21:18.912
Of course I knew
they took the fuel.

21:18.914 --> 21:21.915
That's why
I didn't pay them.

21:21.917 --> 21:25.252
A gambler
never shows his cards.

21:25.254 --> 21:28.021
Till we meet again!
